{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01HfxBUgFHxLwFpCFkYGcgmg","type":"tool_result","content":"The file /Users/david/projects/GSD-T/.gsd-t/progress.md has been updated successfully. (file state is current in your context — no need to Read it back)"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"58ad06dd-2644-4e21-9536-13779b8ab76f","uuid":"6093b835-cc4c-4e38-8f00-b8c2e69026d6","timestamp":"2026-05-18T21:37:40.289Z","tool_use_result":{"filePath":"/Users/david/projects/GSD-T/.gsd-t/progress.md","oldString":"## Status: ACTIVE — M57 PARTITIONED\n## Date: 2026-05-18\n## Version: 3.26.11\n\n## Current Milestone\n\nM57 — CI-Parity Verify Gate. PARTITIONED 2026-05-18.","newString":"## Status: ACTIVE — M57 PLANNED\n## Date: 2026-05-18\n## Version: 3.26.11\n\n## Current Milestone\n\nM57 — CI-Parity Verify Gate. PLANNED 2026-05-18. 10 tasks (5 D1 + 5 D2), 1 parallel wave D1∥D2.","originalFile":"# GSD-T Progress\n\n## Project: GSD-T Framework (@tekyzinc/gsd-t)\n## Status: ACTIVE — M57 PARTITIONED\n## Date: 2026-05-18\n## Version: 3.26.11\n\n## Current Milestone\n\nM57 — CI-Parity Verify Gate. PARTITIONED 2026-05-18. 2 file-disjoint domains (m57-d1-build-coverage-check, m57-d2-ci-command-parity), 1 parallel wave D1∥D2 → integrate → verify → complete-milestone. Contracts: cli-build-coverage-contract.md (DRAFT), ci-parity-contract.md (DRAFT), m57-integration-points.md. Test baseline 2547/2547. DEFINED 2026-05-18. Goal: `gsd-t-verify` reproduces the project's actual CI build instead of assuming local tsc/test parity. Origin: TimeTracking v1.10.12 shipped VERIFIED+COMPLETE+tagged while Cloud Build failed (new `hooks/` dir not in Dockerfile COPY + noImplicitAny regressions passed stale-cache local tsc).\n\n## Milestones\n\n| # | Milestone | Status | Version | Domains |\n|---|-----------|--------|---------|---------|\n| M57 | CI-Parity Verify Gate | PARTITIONED | TBD | 2 file-disjoint domains. **D1 build-coverage-check**: `bin/gsd-t-build-coverage.cjs::checkBuildCoverage({projectDir, baseRef, headRef})` enumerates new top-level paths in the milestone commit range; verifies each is referenced by a `COPY`/`ADD` in `Dockerfile`, an artifact/copy step in `cloudbuild.yaml`, or a path in `.github/workflows/*.yml`; returns `{ok, missing[]}`. CLI `gsd-t build-coverage`. Contract `cli-build-coverage-contract.md`. **D2 ci-command-parity**: `bin/gsd-t-ci-parity.cjs` auto-detects project CI config (`cloudbuild.yaml` steps[].args → `.github/workflows/*.yml` jobs[].steps[].run → `Dockerfile` RUN lines → fallback `package.json` scripts build/typecheck/test), runs exactly those commands locally with build caches cleared (`.tsbuildinfo`, `node_modules/.cache`, tsc incremental), and auto-runs `docker build` when a `Dockerfile` is present (presence is the trigger — no opt-in flag). Contract `ci-parity-contract.md`. **Wire-in**: both become mandatory checks in `commands/gsd-t-verify.md` — failure = verify FAIL (blocks complete-milestone), never warning-only. `templates/CLAUDE-global.md` Pre-Commit Gate updated to reference that CI-parity is enforced by `gsd-t-verify` (not a new self-attested checklist item). **Pair-flag**: backlog #25 (`gsd-t-bench`) canonical eval set must include a synthetic regression of this exact incident when bench ships. **Decisions locked (user)**: CI detection = auto-detect from project files; docker build = auto-run when Dockerfile detected. **SCs**: SC1 `checkBuildCoverage` flags a new-dir-not-COPY'd fixture (the TimeTracking class) with `missing[]` non-empty + exit 4; SC2 `ci-parity` on a project with a Dockerfile runs the real `docker build` and fails on a planted tsc strict regression that a warm-cache local `tsc` would miss; SC3 verify FAILs (blocks complete-milestone) when either check fails — proven by deliberately-broken fixture; SC4 zero regressions on `npm test`; SC5 Red Team GRUDGING PASS ≥5 broken patches caught; SC6 doc-ripple complete (verify.md + CLAUDE-global.md + GSD-T-README + README + help + contracts). **Pre-partition assessment**: 2 file-disjoint domains (D1 `bin/gsd-t-build-coverage.cjs` + contract; D2 `bin/gsd-t-ci-parity.cjs` + contract; shared touch only `commands/gsd-t-verify.md` + `bin/gsd-t.js` CLI dispatch — sequenced at integrate, not parallel-written). 1 parallel wave (D1∥D2) + integrate + verify. Standard partition → plan → execute → integrate → verify flow; no discussion needed (pain pattern + surface well-understood from the post-mortem). |\n| M56 | Verify-Gate CLI Fan-Out + Upper-Stage Briefs | COMPLETE | 3.26.10 | 5 file-disjoint domains. **D1 verify-gate-native-cli-workers**: extend `bin/gsd-t-verify-gate.cjs` Track 2 with native `playwright test`, `npm test`, `gsd-t check-coverage` workers (no Task subagent wrapper); record `M55-baseline-tokens` and `M56-actual-tokens` in `.gsd-t/metrics/` + CHANGELOG delta (closes M55 SC4 retroactively). **D2 upper-stage-brief-kinds**: extend `bin/gsd-t-context-brief.cjs` with 5 new kinds: `partition`, `plan`, `discuss`, `impact`, `milestone` (currently only `execute`/`verify`/`qa`/`red-team`/`design-verify`/`scan`). **D3 upper-stage-command-wirein**: thread brief into `commands/gsd-t-{partition,plan,discuss,impact,milestone}.md` Step 1 via `$BRIEF_PATH` pattern from M55 D4. **D4 quick-debug-wirein**: wire preflight + brief + verify-gate into `commands/gsd-t-quick.md` and `commands/gsd-t-debug.md`. **D5 stream-json-universality-lint**: 3 known gaps (`bin/gsd-t.js:3879 spawnClaudeSession()`, `bin/gsd-t-parallel.cjs:378` cache-warm probe, `bin/gsd-t-ratelimit-probe-worker.cjs:89`) — add `--output-format stream-json --verbose` to all three; extend `gsd-t capture-lint` (or sibling) to mechanically reject any `claude -p` / `spawn('claude', …)` invocation without the flag pair; allowlist (e.g. probe workers) lives in lint config not tribal knowledge. **Falsifiable SCs**: SC1 verify wall-clock < M55's 34s; SC2 first-of-milestone brief shaves 30–60k from each subsequent phase's read-budget (measured); SC3 quick+debug invocations show new mandatory preflight banner; SC4 new lint blocks deliberately broken commit dropping `--output-format stream-json`; SC5 (M55 SC4 retroactive closure) M56 records baseline+actual tokens delta in CHANGELOG; SC6 zero regressions on `npm test`; SC7 Red Team GRUDGING PASS — ≥5 broken patches all caught. **Probe learnings honored**: Sonnet ≥11 / Opus ≥7 cliff-clean on 30k prose fixtures; `peakConcurrency=12` in `.gsd-t/ratelimit-map.json`; probe v3+ classifies 429s via API result envelope NOT regex (M56 must NOT regress to regex). **Versioning**: minor bump 3.25.11 → 3.26.10 on complete-milestone (new feature). **Test baseline**: 2487/2485 unit (M55 carryover, 2 pre-existing env-bleed). **Files (planned, finalized at partition)**: `bin/gsd-t-verify-gate.cjs` (additive Track 2 native workers + token-delta recording), `bin/gsd-t-context-brief.cjs` (5 new kinds), `commands/gsd-t-{partition,plan,discuss,impact,milestone,quick,debug}.md` (additive brief + preflight + verify-gate Step 1), `bin/gsd-t.js` (`spawnClaudeSession` add stream-json), `bin/gsd-t-parallel.cjs:378` (cache-warm probe add stream-json), `bin/gsd-t-ratelimit-probe-worker.cjs:89` (add stream-json), `bin/gsd-t-capture-lint.cjs` (additive `--check-stream-json` mode OR new sibling `bin/gsd-t-stream-json-lint.cjs`), `.gsd-t/metrics/m56-token-baseline.json` (new), `e2e/journeys/m56-*.spec.ts` (new ≥3 specs). **Pre-partition assessment**: medium-complexity (5 file-disjoint domains; D5 lint is the riskiest because it must allowlist probe workers without reopening the loophole). Recommend standard partition → plan → execute flow; no discussion needed (pain pattern + surface well-understood from M55 D4/D5 + M41 capture-lint precedent). |\n| M55 | CLI-Preflight Pattern + Parallel-CLI Substrate + Rate-Limit Map + Context Briefs + Verify Gate | COMPLETE | 3.25.10 | 5 file-disjoint domains, all shipped. D1 cli-preflight (commit bb514db), D2 parallel-cli substrate + 5.57× speedup proof (7b9e013), D3 ratelimit probe + map (a0bef17), D4 context-brief generator (998f373), D5 verify-gate two-track + wire-in + doc ripple (b916d77). Red Team GRUDGING PASS — 6/6 broken patches caught (fce2f18). Verify-gate dogfood: 34s wall-clock vs trailing-3 median 681s (20× margin). 2487/2485 tests (2 pre-existing env-bleed). 8 SCs final: SC1✅ contract STABLE, SC2✅ 5.57× speedup, SC3✅ 3 e2e SC3 specs, SC4⚠️ deferred-by-instrumentation-gap (trailing-3 lacks comparable token totals; M56 first measurement closes retroactively), SC5✅ Sonnet ≥11 / Opus ≥7 measured (peakConcurrency bumped 8→12 in ratelimit-map.json), SC6✅ verify-gate 34s ≤ 340s threshold, SC7✅ Red Team GRUDGING PASS, SC8✅ zero regressions. Archive: `.gsd-t/milestones/m55-cli-preflight-pattern-2026-05-09/`. Charter archived. Contracts copied to archive (still referenced in active `.gsd-t/contracts/`). |\n| M52 | Rigorous User-Journey Coverage + Anti-Drift Test Quality | COMPLETE | 3.23.10 | 2 file-disjoint domains. **D1 m52-d1-journey-coverage-tooling** (5 tasks): `bin/journey-coverage.cjs` listener-detector + `bin/journey-coverage-cli.cjs` (`gsd-t check-coverage`) + `scripts/hooks/pre-commit-journey-coverage` + `bin/gsd-t.js` wiring (`installJourneyCoverageHook`, `--install-journey-hook`) + `journey-coverage-contract.md` (manifest schema + listener catalogue + gap rules + exit codes). **D2 m52-d2-journey-specs-and-fixtures** (5 tasks): 12 inaugural `e2e/journeys/*.spec.ts` + `.gsd-t/journey-manifest.json` + 3 real-data NDJSON fixtures under `e2e/fixtures/journeys/` + `replay-helpers.ts` + Red Team \"Test Pass-Through — Journey Edition\" category. **Cross-domain**: only `bin/gsd-t.js` touched by both — D1 only writes it; D2 only reads. **Checkpoints** (`m52-integration-points.md`): C1 D1 publishes `gsd-t check-coverage` + hook installer + STABLE contract → unblocks D2 manifest authoring; C2 D2 lands 12 specs + populated manifest → unblocks verify; C3 Red Team adversarial pass → unblocks complete-milestone. |\n| 