ctive}` — the message body lives in the transcript JSONL at `transcript_path`, not the payload. Function fell through to `return null`; every assistant_turn frame written since v3.18.14 (M45 D2 ship 2026-04-23) was bodyless. Two weeks of broken capture; viewer correctly rendered empty bubbles. **Fix** (3 new private fns in same file): `_safeTranscriptPath` validates absolute path under `~/.claude/projects/` (path-traversal guard, fails open); `_readFileTail` opens fd, reads last 64 KB, drops mid-line leading partial — cap matches contract §\"Guardrails\" 16 KB content cap with headroom; `_readAssistantFromTranscript` scans tail lines bottom-up, parses each as JSON (skip corrupt), picks the latest `type === 'assistant' && isSidechain !== true` row (sidechain = subagent transcripts that share the orchestrator JSONL), concatenates ALL `text`-type content blocks into a single string (multi-block tail markers preserved), skips tool_use-only rows. `_extractAssistantContent` now reads transcript first; original 3 fallback shapes preserved for legacy/test payloads. **Tests** (`test/m45-d2-conversation-capture.test.js` +11 cases): real-shape JSONL → body extracted, multi-block concatenation, latest-row selection, sidechain skipping, tool_use-only skipping, path-traversal /etc/passwd rejected, relative paths rejected, missing transcript_path falls through, unreadable file → stub, >1 MB transcript reads tail-only (positive control: TAIL-ONLY MARKER reachable in last 64 KB), corrupt JSON line skipped. Repurposed the prior \"stub when no content\" test to cover the new \"stub when no content AND no transcript_path\" doctrine. **Journey spec** (`e2e/journeys/conversation-content.spec.ts`): 7-frame in-session NDJSON fixture writes 3 assistant_turn frames carrying real content with unique markers (one is multi-paragraph with HEAD + TAIL markers); spec navigates to `/transcripts`, asserts `#main-stream .frame.assistant-turn` count = 3, every `.body` non-empty, each carries its expec