{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01S3Fs1uFFFYhiupo2obGUke","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t# Domain: m57-d2-ci-command-parity\n2\t\n3\t## Responsibility\n4\t\n5\tReproduce the project's *actual* CI build locally instead of assuming local\n6\ttsc/test parity. Auto-detect the CI config, run exactly those commands with\n7\tbuild caches cleared, and — when a `Dockerfile` is present — auto-run the real\n8\t`docker build`. This is the other half of the TimeTracking v1.10.12 failure:\n9\t~8 `noImplicitAny` regressions passed a warm-cache local `tsc` but failed CI's\n10\tcold build.\n11\t\n12\t`runCiParity({projectDir, ...})` →\n13\t`{ ok: boolean, detectedSource: string, commands: [{cmd, exitCode, ok}], dockerBuilt: boolean, note?: string }`.\n14\t\n15\t**Locked detection precedence (user decision — do NOT re-derive):**\n16\t1. `cloudbuild.yaml` → `steps[].args` (the real Cloud Build command sequence)\n17\t2. `.github/workflows/*.yml` → `jobs[].steps[].run`\n18\t3. `Dockerfile` → `RUN` lines\n19\t4. fallback → `package.json` `scripts` (`build`, `typecheck`, `test` if present)\n20\t\n21\t**Cache clearing before running detected commands:** remove `*.tsbuildinfo`,\n22\t`node_modules/.cache`, tsc incremental artifacts — so a stale local cache cannot\n23\tmask a regression CI would catch.\n24\t\n25\t**Docker:** `Dockerfile` present → auto-run `docker build` (presence is the\n26\ttrigger; **no opt-in flag** — locked user decision). Absent → skip, record note.\n27\t\n28\t## Owned Files/Directories\n29\t\n30\t- `bin/gsd-t-ci-parity.cjs` — NEW. Detector + cache-clearer + command runner +\n31\t  optional docker build. Exports `runCiParity(...)`. CLI entry. Zero ext deps.\n32\t- `.gsd-t/contracts/ci-parity-contract.md` — NEW. Detection precedence, cache\n33\t  paths cleared, docker trigger rule, return envelope, exit codes.\n34\t- `test/m57-d2-ci-parity.test.js` — NEW. Unit tests incl. SC2 fixture\n35\t  (Dockerfile project + planted tsc strict regression a warm-cache local `tsc`\n36\t  would miss → real `docker build` fails → `ok:false`).\n37\t- `test/fixtures/m57-ci-parity/` — NEW. Synthetic fixtures: cloudbuild-driven,\n38\t  GHA-driven, Dockerfile-RUN-driven, package.json-fallback, planted-regression.\n39\t\n40\t## Shared (sequenced at integrate — NOT written in parallel wave)\n41\t\n42\t- `bin/gsd-t.js` — add `case \"ci-parity\":` dispatch (thin spawnSync, mirrors\n43\t  `verify-gate` at line ~4544) + global-bin propagation arrays. **Integrate.**\n44\t- `commands/gsd-t-verify.md` — add D2 check as a FAIL-blocking gate.\n45\t  **Integrate phase only** (D1 also edits this file).\n46\t\n47\t## NOT Owned (do not modify)\n48\t\n49\t- `bin/gsd-t-build-coverage.cjs` and its contract/tests/fixtures (D1)\n50\t- `bin/gsd-t-verify-gate.cjs`, `bin/cli-preflight.cjs` (M55, read-only ref)\n51\t- `templates/CLAUDE-global.md`, `GSD-T-README.md`, `README.md`,\n52\t  `commands/gsd-t-help.md` — doc-ripple at integrate, not in domain\n53\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01KHR3EZa9UC4cmTnEHjzNKh","session_id":"58ad06dd-2644-4e21-9536-13779b8ab76f","uuid":"7215b4ad-1c8c-440c-b4c3-6842031ce818","timestamp":"2026-05-18T21:38:12.632Z","subagent_type":"general-purpose","task_description":"Validate M57 plan"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_0148ux8xBJ12L4AhN63eMu3Q","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t# Constraints: m57-d2-ci-command-parity\n2\t\n3\t## Must Follow\n4\t\n5\t- Zero external runtime deps — Node built-ins only. No YAML library: parse\n6\t  `cloudbuild.yaml` / `.github/workflows/*.yml` with a minimal line/regex scan\n7\t  sufficient for the `steps[].args` / `jobs[].steps[].run` fields. Document the\n8\t  parse approach's known limits in the contract.\n9\t- `.cjs` module, `'use strict';`, header docblock naming the contract (mirror\n10\t  `bin/gsd-t-verify-gate.cjs`).\n11\t- CLI entry self-invokes (`require.main === module`), `--json` output, exit **4**\n12\t  on `ok:false`, **0** on `ok:true`, **2** on usage error (match D1 / journey\n13\t  CLI convention for consistency).\n14\t- Detection precedence is LOCKED (cloudbuild → workflows → Dockerfile RUN →\n15\t  package.json scripts). Do not add heuristics, do not reorder, do not add an\n16\t  opt-in flag for docker. Presence of `Dockerfile` is the sole docker trigger.\n17\t- Cache clear is mandatory before running detected commands — failing to clear\n18\t  caches reintroduces the exact stale-cache blind spot M57 exists to close.\n19\t- Defensive: missing `docker` binary → record note + treat docker step as\n20\t  skipped-not-failed (so projects without Docker daemon don't hard-fail);\n21\t  missing all CI artifacts AND no package.json scripts → `ok:true` + note.\n22\t- Functions under 30 lines where practical; named helpers per detection source\n23\t  and for the cache-clear step.\n24\t\n25\t## Must Not\n26\t\n27\t- Modify any file outside Owned scope. `bin/gsd-t.js` and\n28\t  `commands/gsd-t-verify.md` are SHARED — integrate-sequenced only, never in\n29\t  the parallel execute wave (D1 also edits both).\n30\t- Import or copy code from the TimeTracking project (INSPECT-only — post-mortem\n31\t  facts in `.gsd-t/progress.md` M57 row define the planted-regression fixture).\n32\t- Add a new npm dependency or a YAML parser dep.\n33\t- Shell out without timeouts — every spawned command (incl. `docker build`)\n34\t  must have a bounded timeout and stream/capture output.\n35\t\n36\t## Must Read Before Using\n37\t\n38\t- `bin/gsd-t.js` lines 4544-4561 (`verify-gate` dispatch) — exact dispatcher\n39\t  pattern to replicate at integrate.\n40\t- `bin/gsd-t.js` ~lines 1181-1185 and ~2480-2485 — global-bin arrays.\n41\t- `.gsd-t/progress.md` M57 row — authoritative SC2 fixture spec (Dockerfile\n42\t  project, planted tsc strict regression a warm-cache local tsc misses, real\n43\t  `docker build` must fail → `ok:false`).\n44\t- `bin/gsd-t-verify-gate.cjs` Track 2 — how detected-command results are\n45\t  shaped/consumed downstream (read-only; informs envelope design for the\n46\t  verify.md wire-in at integrate).\n47\t\n48\t## Dependencies\n49\t\n50\t- Depends on: nothing (file-disjoint from D1; parallel wave).\n51\t- Depended on by: integrate phase (verify.md wire-in + CLI dispatch). No\n52\t  execute-time coupling with D1.\n53\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01KHR3EZa9UC4cmTnEHjzNKh","session_id":"58ad06dd-2644-4e21-9536-13779b8ab76f","uuid":"1665c42b-4448-4ecb-9969-03697493477b","timestamp":"2026-05-18T21:38:12.786Z","subagent_type":"general-purpose","task_description":"Validate M57 plan"}
