{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01SpdUyiZD5T1sxN52zEsDy8","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t# Contract: ci-parity\n2\t\n3\tStatus: DRAFT (flips to STABLE at verify)\n4\tVersion: 0.1.0 (→ 1.0.0 STABLE)\n5\tOwner: m57-d2-ci-command-parity\n6\tConsumers: commands/gsd-t-verify.md (FAIL-blocking gate), `gsd-t ci-parity` CLI\n7\t\n8\t## Purpose\n9\t\n10\tReproduce the project's actual CI build locally instead of assuming local\n11\ttsc/test parity. Closes the TimeTracking v1.10.12 stale-cache blind spot\n12\t(~8 `noImplicitAny` regressions passed warm-cache local tsc, failed CI).\n13\t\n14\t## API\n15\t\n16\t```\n17\trunCiParity({ projectDir, timeoutMs? }) → {\n18\t  ok: boolean,\n19\t  detectedSource: 'cloudbuild' | 'workflows' | 'dockerfile-run' | 'package-scripts' | 'none',\n20\t  commands: [{ cmd: string, exitCode: number, ok: boolean }],\n21\t  dockerBuilt: boolean,        // true only if Dockerfile present AND docker available AND build ran\n22\t  dockerSkippedReason?: string,// 'no-dockerfile' | 'docker-unavailable'\n23\t  note?: string\n24\t}\n25\t```\n26\t\n27\t## Detection Precedence (LOCKED — user decision, do NOT reorder/extend)\n28\t\n29\t1. `cloudbuild.yaml` present → run its `steps[].args` command sequence.\n30\t2. else `.github/workflows/*.yml` present → run `jobs[].steps[].run` commands.\n31\t3. else `Dockerfile` present → run its `RUN` lines.\n32\t4. else `package.json` → run `scripts.build`, `scripts.typecheck`,\n33\t   `scripts.test` (only those that exist, in that order).\n34\t5. none of the above → `detectedSource:'none'`, `ok:true`, `note` set.\n35\t\n36\tParsing is minimal line/regex (no YAML lib). Known limits documented in module\n37\tdocblock + this contract: only the first job's steps for workflows; `args`\n38\tarrays joined with spaces for cloudbuild.\n39\t\n40\t## Cache Clearing (MANDATORY, before running detected commands)\n41\t\n42\tRemove, if present, under `projectDir`:\n43\t- every `*.tsbuildinfo`\n44\t- `node_modules/.cache`\n45\t- tsc incremental output dirs referenced by `tsconfig*.json` `outDir`/\n46\t  `tsBuildInfoFile` (best-effort)\n47\t\n48\tRationale: a warm local cache is exactly what masked the TimeTracking\n49\tregression. Skipping this step reintroduces the defect M57 closes.\n50\t\n51\t## Docker Trigger (LOCKED — no opt-in flag)\n52\t\n53\t`Dockerfile` present → run real `docker build` (bounded timeout, output\n54\tcaptured). The build failing → `ok:false`.\n55\t- `Dockerfile` absent → `dockerBuilt:false`, `dockerSkippedReason:'no-dockerfile'`.\n56\t- `docker` binary missing → `dockerBuilt:false`,\n57\t  `dockerSkippedReason:'docker-unavailable'`, NOT a hard failure (projects on\n58\t  hosts without a Docker daemon must still pass).\n59\t\n60\t## Exit Codes (CLI)\n61\t\n62\t| Code | Meaning |\n63\t|------|---------|\n64\t| 0 | `ok:true` — all detected commands + docker build (if applicable) passed |\n65\t| 4 | `ok:false` — ≥1 detected command failed OR docker build failed |\n66\t| 2 | usage error |\n67\t\n68\t## Success Criterion Binding\n69\t\n70\tSC2: `runCiParity` on a fixture project with a `Dockerfile` and a planted tsc\n71\tstrict regression that a warm-cache local `tsc` would NOT catch runs the real\n72\t`docker build`, which fails → `ok:false`, CLI exit 4.\n73\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01KHR3EZa9UC4cmTnEHjzNKh","session_id":"58ad06dd-2644-4e21-9536-13779b8ab76f","uuid":"3a3cf7d7-1d5b-45c8-8f8c-0c45824892b9","timestamp":"2026-05-18T21:38:13.203Z","subagent_type":"general-purpose","task_description":"Validate M57 plan"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_018bqjcWPEgGE2z3Cq7QSL62","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t# M57 Integration Points\n2\t\n3\tMilestone: M57 — CI-Parity Verify Gate\n4\tDomains: m57-d1-build-coverage-check, m57-d2-ci-command-parity\n5\tWave plan: **1 parallel wave (D1 ∥ D2)** → integrate → verify → complete-milestone\n6\t\n7\t## Dependency Graph\n8\t\n9\t### Wave 1 — Independent (parallel): D1 ∥ D2\n10\t- m57-d1-build-coverage-check: M57-D1-T1 … T5 (intra-domain serial T1→T2→T3→T4→T5)\n11\t- m57-d2-ci-command-parity: M57-D2-T1 … T5 (intra-domain serial T1→T2→T3→T4→T5)\n12\t- **Shared files**: NONE within the wave — D1 and D2 own strictly disjoint files\n13\t- **Cross-domain deps**: NONE — neither domain reads the other's output at execute time\n14\t- **Completes when**: both domains' T5 (contract STABLE) done + tests green\n15\t\n16\t### Integration (serial, after Wave 1)\n17\t- CHECKPOINT C1: D1 execute clean → D1 wire-in unblocked\n18\t- CHECKPOINT C2: D2 execute clean → D2 wire-in unblocked\n19\t- INTEGRATION: serially edit the two SHARED files (`bin/gsd-t.js` dispatch +\n20\t  global-bin arrays; `commands/gsd-t-verify.md` FAIL-blocking gate) — D1 wire-in\n21\t  then D2 wire-in, single agent, no parallelism (same files)\n22\t- CHECKPOINT C3: both wire-ins landed → verify unblocked\n23\t\n24\t### Solo-mode execution order\n25\t1. Wave 1: D1 T1-T5 and D2 T1-T5 (parallel-safe — run concurrently or interleaved)\n26\t2. CHECKPOINT C1 + C2: both domains green\n27\t3. Integration: gsd-t.js dispatch + verify.md gate (serial, single agent)\n28\t4. CHECKPOINT C3\n29\t5. Verify → complete-milestone\n30\t\n31\t## File-Disjointness (parallel wave safety)\n32\t\n33\tD1 and D2 own strictly disjoint files during the execute wave:\n34\t\n35\t| Path | D1 | D2 |\n36\t|------|----|----|\n37\t| `bin/gsd-t-build-coverage.cjs` | ✅ owns | — |\n38\t| `bin/gsd-t-ci-parity.cjs` | — | ✅ owns |\n39\t| `.gsd-t/contracts/cli-build-coverage-contract.md` | ✅ owns | — |\n40\t| `.gsd-t/contracts/ci-parity-contract.md` | — | ✅ owns |\n41\t| `test/m57-d1-build-coverage.test.js` | ✅ owns | — |\n42\t| `test/m57-d2-ci-parity.test.js` | — | ✅ owns |\n43\t| `test/fixtures/m57-build-coverage/**` | ✅ owns | — |\n44\t| `test/fixtures/m57-ci-parity/**` | — | ✅ owns |\n45\t\n46\tNo execute-time cross-domain reads. Both INSPECT `bin/gsd-t-verify-gate.cjs` /\n47\t`bin/gsd-t.js` as read-only pattern reference — no writes during the wave.\n48\t\n49\t`gsd-t parallel --dry-run` MUST report D1∥D2 as file-disjoint at end of plan.\n50\t\n51\t## Shared Files — Integrate-Sequenced (NOT written in the parallel wave)\n52\t\n53\tThese are touched by BOTH domains' wire-ins, so they are written **serially at\n54\tthe integrate phase**, after both D1 and D2 execute cleanly:\n55\t\n56\t### `bin/gsd-t.js`\n57\t- Add `case \"build-coverage\":` and `case \"ci-parity\":` dispatch cases — thin\n58\t  `spawnSync` dispatchers mirroring the `verify-gate` case (lines ~4544-4561).\n59\t- Add `gsd-t-build-coverage.cjs` and `gsd-t-ci-parity.cjs` to the two\n60\t  global-bin propagation arrays (~lines 1181-1185 and ~2480-2485).\n61\t\n62\t### `commands/gsd-t-verify.md`\n63\t- Add **both** D1 and D2 as FAIL-blocking checks. Failure of either = verify\n64\t  **FAIL** → blocks complete-milestone. Never warning-only.\n65\t- Wire near the M55 verify-gate block (Step 2) so CI-parity runs as part of the\n66\t  mandatory gate, not as an optional dimension.\n67\t\n68\t## Doc-Ripple (integrate phase, after wire-in)\n69\t\n70\t- `templates/CLAUDE-global.md` — Pre-Commit Gate: note CI-parity is enforced by\n71\t  `gsd-t-verify` (NOT a new self-attested checklist line — it's mechanically\n72\t  gated). Mirror into live `~/.claude/CLAUDE.md` if the template/live invariant\n73\t  requires it.\n74\t- `GSD-T-README.md` + `README.md` — commands table: add `build-coverage`,\n75\t  `ci-parity`.\n76\t- `commands/gsd-t-help.md` — add both commands.\n77\t- `package.json` — version bump handled at complete-milestone (minor:\n78\t  3.26.11 → 3.27.10, new feature).\n79\t\n80\t## Checkpoints\n81\t\n82\t- **C1** — D1 execute clean (module + contract + tests green) → unblocks D1's\n83\t  integrate wire-in.\n84\t- **C2** — D2 execute clean (module + contract + tests green) → unblocks D2's\n85\t  integrate wire-in.\n86\t- **C3** — Both wire-ins landed in `gsd-t.js` + `gsd-t-verify.md` (serial) →\n87\t  unblocks verify.\n88\t- **C4** — Verify PASS (SC1-SC6, deliberately-broken fixtures prove FAIL path,\n89\t  Red Team GRUDGING PASS ≥5 broken patches caught) → unblocks complete-milestone.\n90\t\n91\t## Pair-Flag (carry to backlog #25)\n92\t\n93\tWhen `gsd-t-bench` (backlog #25) ships, its canonical eval set MUST include a\n94\tsynthetic regression of the TimeTracking v1.10.12 incident (new-dir-not-COPY'd\n95\t+ warm-cache-masked tsc strict regression) to guard against M57 regressing.\n96\tTracked here; no M57 code change required.\n97\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01KHR3EZa9UC4cmTnEHjzNKh","session_id":"58ad06dd-2644-4e21-9536-13779b8ab76f","uuid":"a5c27ceb-0966-495f-b2c1-5c1a82da1810","timestamp":"2026-05-18T21:38:13.329Z","subagent_type":"general-purpose","task_description":"Validate M57 plan"}
