{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01F3XNrM9TPxsFnGGJuk4Hek","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t# Domain: m57-d1-build-coverage-check\n2\t\n3\t## Responsibility\n4\t\n5\tDetect new top-level paths added in a milestone's commit range that are NOT\n6\treferenced by any CI build artifact (Dockerfile `COPY`/`ADD`, `cloudbuild.yaml`\n7\tartifact/copy step, or `.github/workflows/*.yml` path). This is the exact\n8\tTimeTracking v1.10.12 failure class: a new `hooks/` directory was committed but\n9\tabsent from the Dockerfile `COPY` directives, so Cloud Build shipped without it\n10\twhile local verify reported VERIFIED.\n11\t\n12\t`checkBuildCoverage({projectDir, baseRef, headRef})` →\n13\t`{ ok: boolean, missing: string[], checkedAgainst: string[], note?: string }`.\n14\t\n15\t- `ok=false` + non-empty `missing[]` + process exit code **4** when a new\n16\t  top-level path is not covered by any detected CI artifact.\n17\t- `ok=true` when every new top-level path is referenced, OR when no CI artifacts\n18\t  exist at all (nothing to be inconsistent with — record `note`).\n19\t\n20\t## Owned Files/Directories\n21\t\n22\t- `bin/gsd-t-build-coverage.cjs` — NEW. The detector module + CLI entry.\n23\t  Exports `checkBuildCoverage(...)`. Zero external runtime deps (Node built-ins\n24\t  only, per repo zero-dep invariant). `git diff --name-only baseRef..headRef`\n25\t  to enumerate changed paths; collapse to distinct top-level segments; for each,\n26\t  grep the detected CI artifacts for a reference.\n27\t- `.gsd-t/contracts/cli-build-coverage-contract.md` — NEW. Schema for the return\n28\t  envelope, exit codes, CI-artifact reference rules, baseRef/headRef defaulting.\n29\t- `test/m57-d1-build-coverage.test.js` — NEW. Unit tests incl. SC1 fixture\n30\t  (new-dir-not-COPY'd → `missing[]` non-empty + exit 4).\n31\t- `test/fixtures/m57-build-coverage/` — NEW. Synthetic project fixtures\n32\t  (Docker+CloudBuild, GHA-only, no-CI) reproducing the TimeTracking pattern.\n33\t\n34\t## Shared (sequenced at integrate — NOT written in parallel wave)\n35\t\n36\t- `bin/gsd-t.js` — add `case \"build-coverage\":` dispatch (thin spawnSync to\n37\t  `bin/gsd-t-build-coverage.cjs`, mirrors `verify-gate` case at line ~4544) +\n38\t  add `gsd-t-build-coverage.cjs` to the two global-bin propagation arrays\n39\t  (~line 1184 and ~line 2485). **Integrate phase only.**\n40\t- `commands/gsd-t-verify.md` — add D1 check as a FAIL-blocking gate.\n41\t  **Integrate phase only** (D2 also edits this file).\n42\t\n43\t## NOT Owned (do not modify)\n44\t\n45\t- `bin/gsd-t-ci-parity.cjs` and its contract/tests/fixtures (D2)\n46\t- `bin/gsd-t-verify-gate.cjs`, `bin/cli-preflight.cjs` (M55, read-only reference)\n47\t- `templates/CLAUDE-global.md`, `GSD-T-README.md`, `README.md`,\n48\t  `commands/gsd-t-help.md` — doc-ripple at integrate, not in domain\n49\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_013TZF28A2StK6MConWNruRz","session_id":"58ad06dd-2644-4e21-9536-13779b8ab76f","uuid":"67298462-c176-4b68-81b9-0343c0e478bd","timestamp":"2026-05-18T21:39:43.498Z","subagent_type":"general-purpose","task_description":"Execute M57 D1 build-coverage"}
