{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01Kk8xvPNSUn2i8gshNGQawE","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t# Domain: m57-d2-ci-command-parity\n2\t\n3\t## Responsibility\n4\t\n5\tReproduce the project's *actual* CI build locally instead of assuming local\n6\ttsc/test parity. Auto-detect the CI config, run exactly those commands with\n7\tbuild caches cleared, and — when a `Dockerfile` is present — auto-run the real\n8\t`docker build`. This is the other half of the TimeTracking v1.10.12 failure:\n9\t~8 `noImplicitAny` regressions passed a warm-cache local `tsc` but failed CI's\n10\tcold build.\n11\t\n12\t`runCiParity({projectDir, ...})` →\n13\t`{ ok: boolean, detectedSource: string, commands: [{cmd, exitCode, ok}], dockerBuilt: boolean, note?: string }`.\n14\t\n15\t**Locked detection precedence (user decision — do NOT re-derive):**\n16\t1. `cloudbuild.yaml` → `steps[].args` (the real Cloud Build command sequence)\n17\t2. `.github/workflows/*.yml` → `jobs[].steps[].run`\n18\t3. `Dockerfile` → `RUN` lines\n19\t4. fallback → `package.json` `scripts` (`build`, `typecheck`, `test` if present)\n20\t\n21\t**Cache clearing before running detected commands:** remove `*.tsbuildinfo`,\n22\t`node_modules/.cache`, tsc incremental artifacts — so a stale local cache cannot\n23\tmask a regression CI would catch.\n24\t\n25\t**Docker:** `Dockerfile` present → auto-run `docker build` (presence is the\n26\ttrigger; **no opt-in flag** — locked user decision). Absent → skip, record note.\n27\t\n28\t## Owned Files/Directories\n29\t\n30\t- `bin/gsd-t-ci-parity.cjs` — NEW. Detector + cache-clearer + command runner +\n31\t  optional docker build. Exports `runCiParity(...)`. CLI entry. Zero ext deps.\n32\t- `.gsd-t/contracts/ci-parity-contract.md` — NEW. Detection precedence, cache\n33\t  paths cleared, docker trigger rule, return envelope, exit codes.\n34\t- `test/m57-d2-ci-parity.test.js` — NEW. Unit tests incl. SC2 fixture\n35\t  (Dockerfile project + planted tsc strict regression a warm-cache local `tsc`\n36\t  would miss → real `docker build` fails → `ok:false`).\n37\t- `test/fixtures/m57-ci-parity/` — NEW. Synthetic fixtures: cloudbuild-driven,\n38\t  GHA-driven, Dockerfile-RUN-driven, package.json-fallback, planted-regression.\n39\t\n40\t## Shared (sequenced at integrate — NOT written in parallel wave)\n41\t\n42\t- `bin/gsd-t.js` — add `case \"ci-parity\":` dispatch (thin spawnSync, mirrors\n43\t  `verify-gate` at line ~4544) + global-bin propagation arrays. **Integrate.**\n44\t- `commands/gsd-t-verify.md` — add D2 check as a FAIL-blocking gate.\n45\t  **Integrate phase only** (D1 also edits this file).\n46\t\n47\t## NOT Owned (do not modify)\n48\t\n49\t- `bin/gsd-t-build-coverage.cjs` and its contract/tests/fixtures (D1)\n50\t- `bin/gsd-t-verify-gate.cjs`, `bin/cli-preflight.cjs` (M55, read-only ref)\n51\t- `templates/CLAUDE-global.md`, `GSD-T-README.md`, `README.md`,\n52\t  `commands/gsd-t-help.md` — doc-ripple at integrate, not in domain\n53\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_0149nXxtttvom24BpCbenYek","session_id":"58ad06dd-2644-4e21-9536-13779b8ab76f","uuid":"795200a6-cd99-4a4c-b169-d1f25792f6d9","timestamp":"2026-05-18T21:40:02.671Z","subagent_type":"general-purpose","task_description":"Execute M57 D2 ci-parity"}
