{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_018VK8YHEzCVDGbFVutG9uWE","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t# Contract: cli-build-coverage\n2\t\n3\tStatus: STABLE\n4\tVersion: 1.0.0\n5\tOwner: m57-d1-build-coverage-check\n6\tConsumers: commands/gsd-t-verify.md (FAIL-blocking gate), `gsd-t build-coverage` CLI\n7\t\n8\t## Purpose\n9\t\n10\tDetect new top-level paths added in a milestone's commit range that no CI build\n11\tartifact references — the TimeTracking v1.10.12 failure class (new `hooks/` dir\n12\tcommitted, absent from Dockerfile `COPY`, shipped broken while verify passed).\n13\t\n14\t## API\n15\t\n16\t```\n17\tcheckBuildCoverage({ projectDir, baseRef, headRef, _newPaths }) → {\n18\t  ok: boolean,\n19\t  missing: string[],          // top-level paths not referenced by any CI artifact\n20\t  checkedAgainst: string[],   // which CI artifacts were detected & scanned\n21\t  newPaths: string[],         // all new top-level paths in baseRef..headRef\n22\t  note?: string               // set when no CI artifacts exist or diff is empty\n23\t}\n24\t```\n25\t\n26\t- `projectDir` (string, required) — project root.\n27\t- `baseRef` / `headRef` (string, optional) — git refs bounding the milestone\n28\t  commit range. **Default when omitted**: `HEAD~1..HEAD`. (Plan phase MAY refine\n29\t  to a milestone-tag heuristic; the fallback stays `HEAD~1..HEAD`.)\n30\t- `_newPaths` (string[], optional, **test seam**) — when provided, bypasses\n31\t  `git diff --name-only` entirely and uses this list as the set of changed\n32\t  file paths. Callers collapse to top-level segments via the same helper.\n33\t  Intended for unit tests; not exposed via the CLI.\n34\t\n35\t**Throws `UsageError`** (not returned in envelope) when git state is unusable:\n36\tno git repo, bad refs, or identical baseRef/headRef. The CLI catches this and\n37\texits 2. The `checkBuildCoverage` function itself never throws for CI-artifact\n38\tconditions — those are expressed in the return envelope.\n39\t\n40\t## Detection Rules — a new top-level path is \"covered\" if referenced by ANY of:\n41\t\n42\t1. `Dockerfile` — a `COPY` or `ADD` directive whose source path includes the\n43\t   top-level segment (line-based scan). `COPY --from=` (multi-stage image copy)\n44\t   is excluded — those reference image layers, not workspace paths.\n45\t2. `cloudbuild.yaml` — appears in any `steps[].args` or artifact/copy path\n46\t   (line/regex path-segment scan; no YAML lib).\n47\t3. `.github/workflows/*.yml` — appears as a path segment in any workflow file\n48\t   (line/regex path-segment scan; no YAML lib).\n49\t\n50\t`COPY . .` (or `ADD . .`) sets `coversAll:true` → `missing` is always empty\n51\tregardless of what top-level paths appear in the diff.\n52\t\n53\tThe parsers for cloudbuild.yaml and workflow YAML use a heuristic line scan\n54\t(`/\\b([a-zA-Z0-9_.-]+)\\//g`) — any `segment/` pattern in a line is treated as\n55\ta covered path reference. This is intentionally conservative (false positives\n56\tare acceptable; false negatives are not).\n57\t\n58\t## Exit Codes (CLI)\n59\t\n60\t| Code | Meaning |\n61\t|------|---------|\n62\t| 0 | `ok:true` — all new paths covered, OR no CI artifacts exist (`note` set) |\n63\t| 4 | `ok:false` — ≥1 new top-level path uncovered (`missing[]` non-empty) |\n64\t| 2 | usage error (bad args, not a git repo, bad refs) |\n65\t\n66\t## Defensive Behavior\n67\t\n68\t- No git repo / detached HEAD / identical refs → `UsageError` thrown (not\n69\t  returned in envelope); CLI catches and exits 2 with a clear message.\n70\t- No CI artifacts at all → `ok:true`, `note:\"no CI artifacts detected\"`, exit 0\n71\t  (nothing to be inconsistent with — this is not a failure).\n72\t- Empty diff → `ok:true`, `newPaths:[]`, `note:\"empty diff\"`, exit 0.\n73\t\n74\t## Success Criterion Binding\n75\t\n76\tSC1: `checkBuildCoverage` on a fixture where a new `hooks/` dir is committed but\n77\tabsent from the Dockerfile `COPY` directives returns `ok:false`,\n78\t`missing:[\"hooks\"]`, CLI exit code 4.\n79\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_013TZF28A2StK6MConWNruRz","session_id":"58ad06dd-2644-4e21-9536-13779b8ab76f","uuid":"aea2b9f7-6d23-4904-8e40-f0cfd8121669","timestamp":"2026-05-18T21:44:29.170Z","subagent_type":"general-purpose","task_description":"Execute M57 D1 build-coverage"}
