KED decisions (D2 docker auto-runs on Dockerfile presence with NO opt-in flag; cache-clear is mandatory before commands), and D1's SC1 binding + D2's SC2 binding. Report any divergence as a contract violation.\n4. Test-quality audit: read both test files. For each test() block, confirm it asserts functional behavior (correct envelope values, correct exit codes, regression actually caught) — NOT just \"function exists\" / \"no throw\". Flag any shallow test (would pass on a stubbed/empty implementation) as SHALLOW TEST.\n5. Coverage gap audit: are there obvious untested paths in either module's contract? (e.g., D1: COPY . . coversAll, COPY --from= exclusion, empty-diff note, UsageError→exit2; D2: each of the 5 detection sources, cache-clear removes stale .tsbuildinfo, docker-unavailable non-failure, docker-absent non-failure). List any contract-specified behavior with NO corresponding test.\n\nAppend every issue to .gsd-t/qa-issues.md (create with header `| Date | Command | Step | Model | Duration(s) | Severity | Finding |` if missing; date = 2026-05-18).\n\nFinal line, EXACT format:\n`Unit: X/Y pass | E2E: X/Y pass (or N/A) | Contract: compliant/N violations | Shallow tests: N (list) | Coverage gaps: N (list)`\n\nThen a one-word VERDICT: PASS or FAIL. FAIL if any contract violation, shallow test, or untested contract-specified behavior exists."},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":307,"cache_read_input_tokens":129433,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":307},"output_tokens":56,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"58ad06dd-2644-4e21-9536-13779b8ab76f","uuid":"b1d1c6b4-8810-47e7-bd16-8f20939c4ef7","request_id":"req_011CbAmd5GdbzdXBWGK2CPVd"}
