{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_014f5E1QaRnLknxatJFrXstF","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t| Date | Command | Step | Model | Duration(s) | Severity | Finding |\n2\t|------|---------|------|-------|-------------|----------|---------|\n3\t| 2026-04-17 | red-team | M39 W1 | opus | 1200 | CRITICAL | GSD_T_AGENT_ID has no producer — 189 shims write nothing at runtime (D2 feature dead-on-arrival). See .gsd-t/red-team-report.md BUG-1 |\n4\t| 2026-04-17 | red-team | M39 W1 | opus | 1200 | CRITICAL | --worker-timeout CLI flag referenced by contract §16 is not parsed by parseArgs; config.workerTimeoutMs also not merged into opts. No escape hatch for >270s iters. BUG-2 |\n5\t| 2026-04-17 | red-team | M39 W1 | opus | 1200 | HIGH | bin/gsd-t-unattended.js diverged from .cjs — M39 D2/D3/D4 changes landed only in .cjs; .js still has 3600000 default, no Team Mode, no watch-progress banner. BUG-3 |\n6\t| 2026-04-17 | red-team | M39 W1 | opus | 1200 | HIGH | Team Mode prompt + contract §15 reference \"Step 4 Team Mode\" but Team Mode is Step 3 in commands/gsd-t-execute.md. BUG-4 |\n7\t| 2026-04-17 | red-team | M39 W1 | opus | 1200 | MEDIUM | commands/gsd-t-execute.md Step 5.25 shim has truncated --step-label ending \"design contract exist\" (missing \"s)\"). BUG-5 |\n8\t| 2026-04-17 | red-team | M39 W1 | opus | 1200 | MEDIUM | buildTree with cyclic parent_agent_id refs produces empty tree silently (nodes attach to each other's children, never reach roots/orphans). BUG-6 |\n9\t| 2026-04-17 | red-team | M39 W1 | opus | 1200 | LOW | Contract §18 references bin/gsd-t-unattended.js but M39 code lives in .cjs. BUG-7 |\n10\t| 2026-04-17 | red-team | M39 W1 | opus | 1200 | LOW | Contract §13 config.json example still shows workerTimeoutMs: 3600000 (old default). BUG-8 |\n11\t| 2026-05-06 09:03 | gsd-t-plan | Step 7 | haiku | 37 | low | Validator initially flagged REQ traceability (Check 1) as FAIL — root cause: git stash/pop dance during baseline test capture dropped the in-progress append to docs/requirements.md. Re-appended (11 rows REQ-M47-D1-01..07 + REQ-M47-D2-01..04). Re-verified by direct grep. All other 6 checks PASS. |\n12\t| 2026-05-06 11:00 | red-team | M48 | opus | 600 | MEDIUM | `$&` (and other `$`-substitution patterns) in project basename corrupt the rendered title. `String.prototype.replace(/__PROJECT_NAME__/g, _escapeHtml(name))` interprets `$&` in the replacement string as the matched text, re-injecting the placeholder. Project at `/path/name$&literal` renders `<title>name__PROJECT_NAME__amp;literal</title>` instead of `<title>name$&amp;literal</title>`. Fix: use function-form replacement `() => _escapeHtml(projectName)`. See `.gsd-t/red-team-report.md` BUG-1. |\n13\t| 2026-05-06 11:00 | red-team | M48 | opus | 600 | LOW | Legacy `renderTree()` click handler at `gsd-t-transcript.html:872-875` does not guard against in-session entries; siblings of `mainEntry` (older in-session NDJSONs) land in the live bucket and rendering uses the unguarded handler. Click mutates URL hash but `hashchange` early-return prevents bottom-pane pinning. Cosmetic state pollution only. Copy the `if (isInSession) return;` guard from `renderRailEntry`. See BUG-2. |\n14\t| 2026-05-06 11:00 | red-team | M48 | opus | 600 | LOW | Test quality — 14 of 19 M48 tests assert against raw HTML source strings (e.g. `assert.match(html, /new Date\\(frame\\.ts\\)/)`) instead of executing the function and asserting on observable output. A buggy implementation that contained the right tokens but had wrong behaviour would pass. Violates CLAUDE.md § E2E Test Quality Standard. Functional rewrites recommended for Bug 2/3/4 tests. See BUG-3. |\n15\t\n16\t| 2026-05-06 14:01 | gsd-t-execute | Step 5.5 (Red Team) | opus | 302s | HIGH | BUG-1 — `pubspec.yaml`/`tailwind.config.{js,ts}` as directories yielded false positives. FIXED in same cycle (statSync().isFile()). |\n17\t| 2026-05-06 14:01 | gsd-t-execute | Step 5.5 (Red Team) | opus | 302s |