{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_012gZ3dJs9jRp9CBTGAE7ycq","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"All clear. Summary:\n\n**D1 test count: 13 → 15** (added 2 tests)\n\n**Both QA issues resolved:**\n\n1. **MEDIUM SHALLOW TEST (Issue 1)** — The original `checkBuildCoverage return shape has all required fields` test used `_newPaths: []` (empty-diff early-return), so `checkedAgainst` was always `[]` and CI artifact detection code was never exercised. Added a sibling test `checkBuildCoverage return shape: checkedAgainst non-empty when CI artifacts detected` that injects `_newPaths: ['hooks/post-deploy.sh']` against the `docker-cloudbuild` fixture, asserts all envelope keys are present **and** that `checkedAgainst` contains `'Dockerfile'`. A stub that only handles the empty-diff path would return `checkedAgainst: []` and fail this test.\n\n2. **HIGH COVERAGE GAP (Issue 2)** — Added `COPY --from= exclusion: dist covered by --from= layer does NOT prevent missing[]`. The `docker-cloudbuild` fixture Dockerfile contains `COPY --from=builder /app/dist ./dist` at line 10. The test injects `_newPaths: ['dist/bundle.js', 'hooks/x.js']` and asserts `dist` IS in `missing[]` — confirming the `--from=` COPY is correctly excluded from workspace coverage parsing. The implementation already has the exclusion (`/^COPY\\s+--from=/i.test(trimmed)`) and the test passes, proving the exclusion is in effect.\n\n**Full suite: 2587 tests, 2586 pass, 1 self-skip, 0 fail.**"},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: acd3934950a241327 (use SendMessage with to: 'acd3934950a241327' to continue this agent)\n<usage>total_tokens: 40709\ntool_uses: 8\nduration_ms: 87810</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"58ad06dd-2644-4e21-9536-13779b8ab76f","uuid":"16bf22bd-f218-420d-b2b7-dfab84674954","timestamp":"2026-05-18T21:57:11.077Z","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Test-only fix for GSD-T M57 domain D1. Working dir: /Users/david/projects/GSD-T. Branch m57-ci-parity-verify-gate (already checked out — do NOT switch/commit). You may ONLY modify `test/m57-d1-build-coverage.test.js`. Do NOT modify bin/gsd-t-build-coverage.cjs, the contract, fixtures, or any other file.\n\nQA flagged 2 issues in test/m57-d1-build-coverage.test.js — fix both:\n\n1. MEDIUM SHALLOW TEST: `checkBuildCoverage return shape has all required fields` uses `_newPaths:[]` (empty-diff early-return), so `checkedAgainst` is always `[]` and the shape is never exercised when CI artifacts ARE detected. FIX: strengthen (or add a sibling test) so the return-shape assertion runs on a case where CI artifacts ARE detected and `checkedAgainst` is non-empty — assert all envelope keys present AND that `checkedAgainst` contains the detected artifact(s) for the `docker-cloudbuild` fixture (or equivalent). It must fail on a stub that only handles the empty-diff path.\n\n2. HIGH COVERAGE GAP: No test for `COPY --from=` exclusion. The `docker-cloudbuild` fixture Dockerfile contains `COPY --from=builder /app/dist ./dist`. Contract says `COPY --from=` is excluded (image layers, not workspace paths). ADD a test that, with `dist` among the new top-level paths (use the `_newPaths` test seam to inject e.g. `['dist/bundle.js','hooks/x.js']` against the docker-cloudbuild fixture projectDir), asserts `dist` IS in `missing[]` (i.e., the `--from=` COPY does NOT count as covering `dist`). This proves the exclusion is in effect. Verify the fixture's Dockerfile actually contains a `COPY --from=` line first (read it); if it does not, add the assertion using whatever fixture does — do not modify fixtures.\n\nAfter editing: run `node --test test/m57-d1-build-coverage.test.js` (all must pass), then `npm test` (full suite — must stay green, expect ~2585 tests / 1 self-skip / 0 fail). If a new test fails because the implementation is actually wrong, STOP and report the discrepancy precisely (do NOT modify the implementation — that's a contract/feature issue for the lead). Otherwise report: D1 test count before/after, full npm test tail, and confirmation both QA issues are now covered by failing-on-stub assertions.","agentId":"acd3934950a241327","agentType":"general-purpose","content":[{"type":"text","text":"All clear. Summary:\n\n**D1 test count: 13 → 15** (added 2 tests)\n\n**Both QA issues resolved:**\n\n1. **MEDIUM SHALLOW TEST (Issue 1)** — The original `checkBuildCoverage return shape has all required fields` test used `_newPaths: []` (empty-diff early-return), so `checkedAgainst` was always `[]` and CI artifact detection code was never exercised. Added a sibling test `checkBuildCoverage return shape: checkedAgainst non-empty when CI artifacts detected` that injects `_newPaths: ['hooks/post-deploy.sh']` against the `docker-cloudbuild` fixture, asserts all envelope keys are present **and** that `checkedAgainst` contains `'Dockerfile'`. A stub that only handles the empty-diff path would return `checkedAgainst: []` and fail this test.\n\n2. **HIGH COVERAGE GAP (Issue 2)** — Added `COPY --from= exclusion: dist covered by --from= layer does NOT prevent missing[]`. The `docker-cloudbuild` fixture Dockerfile contains `COPY --from=builder /app/dist ./dist` at line 10. The test injects `_newPaths: ['dist/bundle.js', 'hooks/x.js']` and asserts `dist` IS in `missing[]` — confirming the `--from=` COPY is correctly excluded from workspace coverage parsing. The implementation already has the exclusion (`/^COPY\\s+--from=/i.test(trimmed)`) and the test passes, proving the exclusion is in effect.\n\n**Full suite: 2587 tests, 2586 pass, 1 self-skip, 0 fail.**"}],"totalDurationMs":87810,"totalTokens":40709,"totalToolUseCount":8,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":721,"cache_read_input_tokens":39572,"output_tokens":415,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":721},"inference_geo":"","iterations