{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01XvmJcXCY9Z93dXSSMyPSUp","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect. Now let me create the final verification summary:\n\nSunday: May 18, 2026 14:15 UTC — GSD-T v3.26.11 — CURRENT\n\n## QA Re-Verification: M57 Fix Cycle 1 — PASS\n\n**All 5 QA issues are genuinely resolved** (not papered over). Full test suite confirms.\n\n### Verification Results\n\n| Issue | Test File | Lines | Status | Functional? |\n|-------|-----------|-------|--------|------------|\n| **1** D1 checkBuildCoverage shallow return shape | m57-d1-build-coverage.test.js | 309–330 | **FIXED** | ✓ Assert checkedAgainst non-empty when CI artifacts detected (docker-cloudbuild + non-empty diff). Fails on stub handling empty-diff path only. |\n| **2** D1 COPY --from= untested | m57-d1-build-coverage.test.js | 336–356 | **FIXED** | ✓ Inject dist (via --from=) + hooks (genuine) into docker-cloudbuild. Assert dist IN missing[] (--from= excluded), ok:false. Functional. |\n| **3** D2 docker_unavailable misnamed (actually tested no-dockerfile) | m57-d2-ci-parity.test.js | 184–214 | **FIXED** | ✓ Real path: Dockerfile present + PATH override to unreachable location. Assert ok:true, dockerBuilt:false, dockerSkippedReason:'docker-unavailable'. Not skipped. |\n| **4** D2 separate no-dockerfile test missing | m57-d2-ci-parity.test.js | 176–182 | **FIXED** | ✓ Distinct test: pkg-fallback (no Dockerfile). Assert dockerSkippedReason:'no-dockerfile'. |\n| **5** D2 cli_json_output_has_correct_shape shallow (key existence only) | m57-d2-ci-parity.test.js | 342–356 | **FIXED** | ✓ Now asserts value **types** and **values**: `typeof out.ok==='boolean'`, `out.detectedSource==='package-scripts'`, `Array.isArray(out.commands)`, `typeof out.dockerBuilt==='boolean'`. Fails on `{ok:null, detectedSource:'', ...}`. |\n\n### Test Suite Results\n\n**M57 Test Files Only:**\n```\n✔ 36 tests PASS\n✔ 1 test SKIP (by design: SC2_planted_regression_docker_build_fails — Docker daemon unavailable, Docker-independent checks already validated)\n✔ 0 tests FAIL\n```\n\n**Full Suite (all 360 suites, 2587 tests):**\n```\nℹ pass 2586\nℹ fail 0\nℹ skipped 1 (the expected Docker-dependent SC2 test)\n```\n\n### Per-Issue Deep Dive\n\n**Issue 1 — Shallow checkedAgainst coverage:**\n- **Old path**: Test used empty-diff (`_newPaths:[]`), which early-returns with `checkedAgainst:[]`.\n- **New path (309–330)**: Uses docker-cloudbuild + non-empty diff (`_newPaths: ['hooks/post-deploy.sh']`).\n  - Asserts: `checkedAgainst.length > 0`, `.includes('Dockerfile')`.\n  - **Would FAIL** on a stub that only handles empty-diff path.\n\n**Issue 2 — COPY --from= never verified:**\n- **Old state**: No test existed.\n- **New test (336–356)**: Injects `dist/bundle.js` (covered only by `COPY --from=builder`) + `hooks/x.js` (genuinely uncovered).\n  - Asserts: `dist` IN `missing[]` (proving `--from=` exclusion), `hooks` also in `missing[]`, `ok:false`.\n  - **Would FAIL** on an impl that counted `COPY --from=` lines as workspace coverage.\n\n**Issue 3 — docker_unavailable path never actually tested:**\n- **Old test name/reality mismatch**: Named \"docker_unavailable_is_not_hard_failure\" but code comment explicitly says \"We can't inject _newPaths via CLI, so we need a test approach... we test the API path (above) proves ok:false + missing:[\"hooks\"]... For the CLI exit-4 test... But that's environment-dependent. Better: test the API path... we instead verify exit 4 via a small synthetic git repo.\" — **was testing no-dockerfile, not docker-unavailable**.\n- **New path (184–214)**: Real docker-unavailable state via PATH override.\n  - Sets up Dockerfile present, overrides `process.env.PATH = '/nonexistent-gsd-t-test-path'`.\n  - Asserts: `ok:true` (not hard failure), `dockerBuilt:false`, `dockerSkippedReason:'docker-unavailable'`.\n  - **Would FAIL** on an impl that set `ok:false` for docker-unavailable.\n  - **Runs unconditionally** (not skipped on Docker-less host).\n\n**Issue 4 — No separate no-dockerfile test (distinct coverage):**\n- **New test (176–182)**: `no_dockerfile_skips_docker_non_failure` — uses pkg-fallback fixture (no Dockerfile).\n  - Asserts: `dockerBuilt:false`, `dockerSkippedReason:'no-dockerfile'`.\n  - Separate from docker_unavailable test (Issue 3).\n\n**Issue 5 — JSON output shape shallow (key existence only):**\n- **Old assertion**: `'ok' in r`, `'detectedSource' in r`, `'commands' in r`, `'dockerBuilt' in r` — only checks **key presence**, not types or values.\n- **New assertions (342–356)**:\n  - `typeof out.ok === 'boolean'` — type assertion\n  - `out.detectedSource === 'package-scripts'` — **value** assertion\n  - `Array.isArray(out.commands)` — type assertion\n  - `typeof out.dockerBuilt === 'boolean'` — type assertion\n  - **Would FAIL** on `{ok:null, detectedSource:'', commands:null, dockerBuilt:null}` or `{ok:0, detectedSource:'default', commands:'[]', dockerBuilt:0}`.\n\n### Status Update\n\n**Appended to `.gsd-t/qa-issues.md` (2026-05-18):**\nAll 5 issues resolved with functional assertions. Unit test suite: 36/36 M57 tests PASS, 1 by-design SKIP.\n\n---\n\n**Final Verdict:** `Unit: 36/36 pass | Issues resolved: 5/5 | Still open: 0` — **PASS**"},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: a9e8b874383546c4e (use SendMessage with to: 'a9e8b874383546c4e' to continue this agent)\n<usage>total_tokens: 75341\ntool_uses: 9\nduration_ms: 164669</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"58ad06dd-2644-4e21-9536-13779b8ab76f","uuid":"ddb2d633-6094-4f6b-b90e-83bffa85bdc3","timestamp":"2026-05-18T22:01:29.637Z","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"QA re-verification of fix cycle 1 for GSD-T M57. Working dir: /Users/david/projects/GSD-T.\n\n5 QA issues were flagged and fixed (test-only changes to test/m57-d1-build-coverage.test.js and test/m57-d2-ci-parity.test.js). Verify each is genuinely resolved (not papered over):\n\n1. D1 — `checkBuildCoverage return shape` was s